  "local_port": 51482,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, your ability to see who has viewed your video depends on the type of video you've posted. Here's a breakdown of how it works for different video formats on Instagram:\n\n### 1. **Instagram Stories**\n- **Visibility of Viewers:** **Yes**, you can see exactly who has viewed your Story videos.\n- **How to Check:**\n  1. Open the Instagram app and tap on your profile picture at the top of the feed to view your Story.\n  2. Once your Story is open, swipe up on the screen.\n  3. A list of usernames who have viewed your Story will appear.\n\n### 2. **Instagram Reels**\n- **Visibility of Viewers:** **Limited**. You can see the total number of views, but Instagram does not provide a detailed list of individual users who have watched your Reels.\n- **How to Check:**\n  1. Go to your Reels tab on your profile.\n  2. Tap on a specific Reel.\n  3. Below the Reel, you'll see the view count, but individual viewer identities are not disclosed.\n\n### 3. **Regular Video Posts (Feed Posts)**\n- **Visibility of Viewers:** **No**. Instagram shows the total number of views, but does not provide a list of who exactly has watched your video.\n- **How to Check:**\n  1. Navigate to your profile and select the video post.\n  2. Below the video, the view count is displayed, but tapping it will not reveal specific viewers.\n\n### 4. **IGTV Videos**\n- **Visibility of Viewers:** **No**. Similar to regular feed posts and Reels, IGTV provides view counts without detailed viewer information.\n- **How to Check:**\n  1. Open the IGTV video from your profile.\n  2. View counts are visible below the video, but individual viewer details are not available.\n\n### **Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Privacy Policies:** Instagram prioritizes user privacy, which is why detailed viewer information is limited to Stories. Regular posts, Reels, and IGTV content only show aggregate view counts.\n  \n- **Third-Party Apps Caution:** Be cautious of any third-party apps or services that claim to provide detailed insights into who has viewed your videos or profile. These are often unreliable and can pose security risks, including compromising your Instagram account.\n\n### **Enhancing Engagement:**\n\nWhile you might not be able to see exactly who is viewing all your video content, you can still boost engagement and gain insights through other means:\n\n- **Use Instagram Insights:** If you have a **Business** or **Creator** account, Instagram Insights provides valuable analytics about your audience, including overall reach, impressions, and engagement metrics.\n  \n- **Engage with Your Audience:** Encourage viewers to like, comment, and share your videos. Interacting with your audience can help increase visibility and engagement.\n\n- **Leverage Hashtags and Tags:** Using relevant hashtags and tagging other users can expand the reach of your videos to a broader audience.\n\n- **Consistent Posting:** Regularly post high-quality content to keep your audience engaged and attract new viewers.\n\n### **How to Convert to a Business or Creator Account:**\n\n1. **Go to Your Profile:** Tap the three horizontal lines (menu) in the top-right corner.\n2. **Settings:** Select \"Settings\" at the bottom of the menu.\n3. **Account:** Tap on \"Account.\"\n4. **Switch Account Type:** Choose \"Switch to Professional Account\" and follow the prompts to select either a Business or Creator account.\n\nBy switching, you'll gain access to Instagram Insights and other tools that can help you better understand and engage with your audience.\n\n---\n\nIf you have any more questions about Instagram features or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
